title: Ali Gohar Khan Mahar wins NA-199 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians’ Ali Gohar Khan Mahar has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-199-Ghotki by securing 154,832 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was JUI-P’s Abdul Qayum, who bagged 402,04 votes.
Voters’ turnout remained 46.92 percent.
